now painted in the sky,

00:44:09.396 --> 00:44:15.569 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What a beautiful canvas
you’ve laid before my eyes!

00:44:15.569 --> 00:44:20.741 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The sound of the river
running into the night,

00:44:20.741 --> 00:44:25.813 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The stars are dancing
in the moon’s spotlight—

00:44:25.813 --> 00:44:31.085 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What did I do
To see such beauty?

00:44:31.085 --> 00:44:37.057 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But I know what to do
To show how much I care.

00:44:37.057 --> 00:44:42.763 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’ve got to be thankful,
Tell Jehovah in prayer

00:44:42.763 --> 00:44:48.635 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That I’m thankful
For the love that he shares.

00:44:48.635 --> 00:44:51.638 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Stop,
look around,

00:44:51.638 --> 00:44:56.176 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Take a moment,
and let it sink down in my heart.

00:44:56.176 --> 00:45:02.082 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Never take for granted 
all he’s done.

00:45:02.082 --> 00:45:05.986 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’ve got to be thankful.

00:45:09.089 --> 00:45:12.626 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I see your wisdom
and your strength,

00:45:12.626 --> 00:45:19.099 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Your goodness in ev’rything,
And how much you love.

00:45:19.099 --> 00:45:26.440 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And I’m so thankful;
I’ve got to be thankful.

00:45:46.860 --> 00:45:53.534 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’ve got to be thankful,
Tell Jehovah in prayer

00:45:53.534 --> 00:45:59.640 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That I’m thankful
For the love that he shares.

00:45:59.640 --> 00:46:02.042 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Stop,
look around,

00:46:02.042 --> 00:46:07.314 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Take a moment,
and let it sink down in my heart.

00:46:07.314 --> 00:46:12.419 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Never take for granted
all he’s done.

00:46:12.419 --> 00:46:23.330 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’ve got to be thankful.
I’ve got to be thankful.

00:46:23.330 --> 00:46:29.403 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We’ve got to be thankful.

00:46:40.347 --> 00:46:44.818 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Did you notice one way
of expressing our gratitude to Jehovah?

00:46:44.818 --> 00:46:47.654 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yes, by means of prayer.

00:46:47.654 --> 00:46:51.358 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Having that channel
to the Sovereign of the universe

00:46:51.358 --> 00:46:55.062 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is a benefit of being his people.

00:46:55.062 --> 00:46:58.499 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And speaking of being Jehovah’s people,

00:46:58.499 --> 00:47:00.634 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in last month’s program,

00:47:00.634 --> 00:47:04.204 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we had an opportunity
to visit one of the museums

00:47:04.204 --> 00:47:07.374 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
at world headquarters in Warwick, New York.

00:47:07.374 --> 00:47:09.543 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But there’s more to see.

00:47:09.543 --> 00:47:14.448 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s join Brother John Ekrann,
a helper to the Coordinators’ Committee,

00:47:14.448 --> 00:47:17.351 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
on another visit, and this time,

00:47:17.351 --> 00:47:22.356 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we’ll stop by a museum called
“A People for Jehovah’s Name.”

00:47:27.594 --> 00:47:30.097 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Do you enjoy a good story?

00:47:30.097 --> 00:47:33.267 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
If so, you’re in for a special treat.

00:47:33.267 --> 00:47:35.469 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“A People for Jehovah’s Name”

00:47:35.469 --> 00:47:39.773 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
at world headquarters in Warwick
is more than a history museum.

00:47:40.941 --> 00:47:44.778 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s the modern-day story of a people
seeking to know the true God

00:47:44.778 --> 00:47:46.780 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and to do his will.

00:47:46.780 --> 00:47:48.882 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But this isn’t just any story

00:47:48.882 --> 00:47:50.884 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—it’s our story.

00:47:50.884 --> 00:47:53.954 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So let’s take
a thrilling journey back in time.

00:47:55.656 --> 00:47:58.025 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The story unfolds on the narrative wall

00:47:58.025 --> 00:48:00.294 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and in several galleries along the way.

00:48:01.862 --> 00:48:03.864 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We begin in the 1870’s,

00:48:03.864 --> 00:48:06.533 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when a small group
in Allegheny, Pennsylvania,

00:48:06.533 --> 00:48:09.336 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
decided to reexamine the Bible.

00:48:09.336 --> 00:48:12.139 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
As C. T. Russell reasoned:

00:48:12.139 --> 00:48:14.308 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
All the creeds of Christendom

00:48:14.308 --> 00:48:16.310 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
claim to be founded on the Bible;

00:48:16.310 --> 00:48:18.512 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and these are conflicting.

00:48:18.512 --> 00:48:22.749 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Is it possible that the Bible
has been misrepresented?

00:48:22.749 --> 00:48:26.520 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The more they learned,
the more they wanted to share.

00:48:26.520 --> 00:48:28.522 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So in 1879,

00:48:28.522 --> 00:48:30.857 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
they began publishing Zion’s Watch Tower.

00:48:32.359 --> 00:48:36.496 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Readers were soon taking a stand
for the truths that they were learning.

00:48:36.496 --> 00:48:38.231 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Listen.

00:48:38.231 --> 00:48:41.201 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What I want to tell you is this,

00:48:41.201 --> 00:48:43.270 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I am free!

00:48:43.270 --> 00:48:46.239 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The truth has made me free!

00:48:46.239 --> 00:48:49.876 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
To-day I was excluded
from the Baptist church . . .

00:48:49.876 --> 00:48:54.748 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So I am all alone in the ‘flesh,’
but not in the ‘spirit.’

00:48:56.116 --> 00:48:58.952 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They became known as the Bible Students,

00:48:58.952 --> 00:49:02.956 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and they soon realized that people
everywhere should hear the good news.

00:49:04.358 --> 00:49:08.362 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But how could this small group
preach the Bible’s message earthwide?

00:49:10.097 --> 00:49:12.899 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Transcontinental and international tours

00:49:12.899 --> 00:49:15.035 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
helped them to see how they could expand

00:49:15.035 --> 00:49:17.704 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
their preaching work even further.

00:49:17.704 --> 00:49:19.706 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In just one tour

00:49:19.706 --> 00:49:22.209 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
beginning in December 1911,

00:49:22.209 --> 00:49:24.544 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
C. T. Russell and his associates

00:49:24.544 --> 00:49:27.547 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
traveled completely around the world.

00:49:27.547 --> 00:49:32.386 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s imagine what it was like
to live in those exciting times.

00:49:33.954 --> 00:49:37.290 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In this gallery,
you can experience what life was like

00:49:37.290 --> 00:49:41.728 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for a pilgrim,
or what we today call a circuit overseer.

00:49:41.728 --> 00:49:46.400 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Here’s a pilgrim’s formal jacket
that he’d wear when giving a public talk.

00:49:47.668 --> 00:49:51.772 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Bible Students offered the Studies
in the Scriptures series in the ministry.

00:49:51.772 --> 00:49:54.608 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And they carried lists to locate

00:49:54.608 --> 00:49:57.110 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and visit Watch Tower subscribers.

00:49:57.110 --> 00:49:59.813 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Then in 1914,

00:49:59.813 --> 00:50:03.950 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
they presented
the exciting “Photo-Drama of Creation.”

00:50:03.950 --> 00:50:07.320 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Its purpose was to build faith in the Bible

00:50:07.320 --> 00:50:10.157 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
as God’s inspired Word.

00:50:10.157 --> 00:50:13.026 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It was an innovative combination

00:50:13.026 --> 00:50:15.128 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of moving pictures,

00:50:15.128 --> 00:50:17.330 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
sound recordings,

00:50:17.330 --> 00:50:19.966 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and beautiful, hand-colored glass slides.

00:50:21.001 --> 00:50:24.705 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Hundreds of people reenacted Bible scenes,

00:50:24.705 --> 00:50:27.674 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
some with live animals!

00:50:27.674 --> 00:50:32.512 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Was this enormous work worth all the effort?

00:50:32.512 --> 00:50:35.816 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
DEAR BROTHER RUSSELL,
I want to thank you;

00:50:35.816 --> 00:50:38.452 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
oh, . . . so much, for the privilege

00:50:38.452 --> 00:50:41.621 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of seeing the PHOTO-DRAMA OF CREATION!

00:50:41.621 --> 00:50:44.024 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I had never thought to live to see

00:50:44.024 --> 00:50:47.461 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the everlasting Gospel preached
to those who dwell on the earth . . . !

00:50:47.461 --> 00:50:49.463 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yet so it is.

00:50:49.463 --> 00:50:53.033 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Words cannot tell you how my heart rejoices!

00:50:53.033 --> 00:50:56.203 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—Your sister, F. E. Riley.

00:50:56.203 --> 00:51:00.741 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
By the end of 1914,
over nine million had viewed it.

00:51:02.008 --> 00:51:04.010 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But with such success,

00:51:04.010 --> 00:51:08.415 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the Bible Students didn’t realize
what tests lay ahead.

00:51:14.221 --> 00:51:16.923 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Gentile Times have ended;

00:51:16.923 --> 00:51:20.327 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
their kings have had their day!

00:51:20.327 --> 00:51:23.530 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So we know not what awaits us.

00:51:26.867 --> 00:51:29.369 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
World War I broke out in 1914.

00:51:29.369 --> 00:51:31.204 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Then in 1916,

00:51:31.204 --> 00:51:35.709 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the death of C. T. Russell
left the Bible Students in shock.

00:51:35.709 --> 00:51:38.712 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It was a unique time of testing.

00:51:39.946 --> 00:51:41.948 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Inside the organization,

00:51:41.948 --> 00:51:44.618 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
some struggled over who should take the lead.

00:51:44.618 --> 00:51:46.620 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Outside,

00:51:46.620 --> 00:51:50.056 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
governments tried to force them
to take sides in the war.

00:51:51.258 --> 00:51:53.393 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Then in 1918,

00:51:53.393 --> 00:51:56.696 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
J. F. Rutherford
and seven of his close associates

00:51:56.696 --> 00:51:58.698 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
were imprisoned.

00:51:58.698 --> 00:52:02.202 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Was this the end for the Bible Students?

00:52:02.202 --> 00:52:04.271 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Or would they prove to be

00:52:04.271 --> 00:52:07.207 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
a people for Jehovah’s name?

00:52:07.207 --> 00:52:10.911 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The joy that came
with the release of our brothers

00:52:10.911 --> 00:52:13.413 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from the Atlanta Federal Prison on Tuesday,

00:52:13.413 --> 00:52:18.151 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
March 25, 1919, knew no bounds.

00:52:18.151 --> 00:52:22.289 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Their further devotion to Jehovah
was shown in the fact

00:52:22.289 --> 00:52:24.624 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that they immediately set to work to herald

00:52:24.624 --> 00:52:27.460 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
forth to the people of God everywhere

00:52:27.460 --> 00:52:29.830 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the knowledge of Jehovah’s deliverance.

00:52:29.830 --> 00:52:31.898 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—Thomas Sullivan.

00:52:31.898 --> 00:52:36.102 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Bible Students
moved forward with renewed zeal.

00:52:36.102 --> 00:52:39.272 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But the opposition didn’t end there.

00:52:41.975 --> 00:52:45.278 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In this gallery,
you will see how our brothers and sisters

00:52:45.278 --> 00:52:47.614 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
have stood firm for their faith.

00:52:48.849 --> 00:52:52.118 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In Russia, a father imprisoned for ten years

00:52:52.118 --> 00:52:54.120 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
encouraged his young daughters

00:52:54.120 --> 00:52:56.923 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with hand-drawn postcards.

00:52:56.923 --> 00:52:59.125 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In Greece,

00:52:59.125 --> 00:53:01.928 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
a son used the same blanket in prison

00:53:01.928 --> 00:53:05.365 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that his father used
when imprisoned before him.

00:53:05.365 --> 00:53:09.169 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It was an encouraging reminder
of his father’s integrity.

00:53:09.169 --> 00:53:11.204 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In Korea,

00:53:11.204 --> 00:53:13.273 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Witnesses were locked in tiny cells

00:53:13.273 --> 00:53:17.777 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for up to 30 days at a time.

00:53:17.777 --> 00:53:22.382 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When you stand in the lighted outline,
you get a sense of what it was like.

00:53:24.384 --> 00:53:27.787 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
All of these brothers and sisters
looked beyond the prison bars

00:53:27.787 --> 00:53:30.390 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to their firm hope for the future.

00:53:32.726 --> 00:53:34.861 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
As light from God’s Word increased,

00:53:34.861 --> 00:53:36.863 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the Bible Students humbly let go

00:53:36.863 --> 00:53:41.067 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of cherished but unscriptural traditions.

00:53:41.067 --> 00:53:45.171 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Songs used in worship were examined
in the light of what the Bible taught.

00:53:46.640 --> 00:53:50.343 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The people for Jehovah’s name
were becoming even more evident.

00:53:50.343 --> 00:53:51.978 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So in 1931,

00:53:51.978 --> 00:53:55.649 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
they were thrilled to take on their new name

00:53:55.649 --> 00:53:57.884 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—Jehovah’s Witnesses.

00:53:59.352 --> 00:54:01.354 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Then in 1935,

00:54:01.354 --> 00:54:04.991 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brother Rutherford identified
the great multitude of other sheep,

00:54:04.991 --> 00:54:07.560 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who served alongside the anointed.

00:54:07.560 --> 00:54:11.264 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
At the climax of his talk, he asked:

00:54:11.264 --> 00:54:15.702 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Will all those who have the hope
of living forever on the earth please stand?

00:54:16.903 --> 00:54:18.905 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
With this new understanding,

00:54:18.905 --> 00:54:23.510 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
they saw the true scope
of Jesus’ commission to make disciples.

00:54:23.510 --> 00:54:26.846 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
New and innovative methods were needed.

00:54:28.715 --> 00:54:33.720 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our third gallery shows the preaching
methods used in the 1930’s and 1940’s.

00:54:35.021 --> 00:54:38.625 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Radio was a powerful way
to spread the Kingdom message

00:54:38.625 --> 00:54:40.260 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to large audiences.

00:54:41.895 --> 00:54:44.431 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They also used large phonographs,

00:54:44.431 --> 00:54:47.267 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
called portable transcription machines,

00:54:47.267 --> 00:54:50.036 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with loudspeakers mounted on sound cars.

00:54:51.705 --> 00:54:54.708 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brothers played recorded talks
wherever people gathered.

00:54:55.942 --> 00:55:00.647 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Lighter phonographs
were also designed and produced so publishers

00:55:00.647 --> 00:55:04.551 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
could take the recorded message
directly to people at home.

00:55:04.551 --> 00:55:08.555 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
These methods 
helped bring unity to the message,

00:55:08.555 --> 00:55:12.258 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but the time had come to train each one

00:55:12.258 --> 00:55:15.962 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of Jehovah’s people
to be an effective Witness.

00:55:15.962 --> 00:55:17.964 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Schools were started.

00:55:17.964 --> 00:55:19.599 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Course in Theocratic Ministry

00:55:19.599 --> 00:55:22.335 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
trained publishers in the congregation.

00:55:22.335 --> 00:55:24.838 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And the Bible School of Gilead

00:55:24.838 --> 00:55:28.074 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
began training missionaries
for global expansion.

00:55:28.908 --> 00:55:34.114 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We had entered
into a new era of divine education.

00:55:35.015 --> 00:55:38.451 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And we were about to receive an amazing tool.

00:55:39.686 --> 00:55:41.688 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In 1950,

00:55:41.688 --> 00:55:45.291 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we received the New World Translation
of the Christian Greek Scriptures.

00:55:45.291 --> 00:55:49.929 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And by 1961, the complete Bible was released.

00:55:49.929 --> 00:55:53.133 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Since then,
we’ve seen our tools continue to improve

00:55:53.133 --> 00:55:55.335 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with the wise use of modern technology.

00:55:56.636 --> 00:55:59.606 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
From high-speed printing
to the Internet and video,

00:55:59.606 --> 00:56:02.642 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
these methods help us to stay unified,

00:56:02.642 --> 00:56:04.644 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to reach millions with the good news,

00:56:04.644 --> 00:56:07.113 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and to glorify God.

00:56:07.113 --> 00:56:10.350 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yes, this museum’s story is about people,

00:56:10.350 --> 00:56:12.385 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but not just any people.

00:56:12.385 --> 00:56:15.822 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We are “a people for Jehovah’s name.”

00:56:15.822 --> 00:56:17.957 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Only one question remains:

00:56:17.957 --> 00:56:21.561 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What will you contribute
to this wonderful story?

00:56:23.029 --> 00:56:25.532 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This month, after discussing the theme

00:56:25.532 --> 00:56:28.001 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Cherish Your Privilege of Prayer,”

00:56:28.001 --> 00:56:30.003 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we saw how we should act

00:56:30.003 --> 00:56:33.206 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when we encounter spiritism.

00:56:33.206 --> 00:56:36.309 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When counteracting wicked spirits,

00:56:36.309 --> 00:56:39.746 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
praying for Jehovah’s guidance
is very important.

00:56:40.914 --> 00:56:44.584 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Next, Brother Morris
showed us the importance of praying

00:56:44.584 --> 00:56:46.619 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to protect our heart.

00:56:46.619 --> 00:56:48.621 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And the music video

00:56:48.621 --> 00:56:52.592 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
reminded us
of not forgetting to thank Jehovah

00:56:52.592 --> 00:56:54.594 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for everything he’s given us.

00:56:56.129 --> 00:56:58.698 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The provision of communicating with Jehovah

00:56:58.698 --> 00:57:02.569 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is a privilege we have of being his people.

00:57:02.569 --> 00:57:05.672 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A visit to Warwick Bethel
showed us how Jehovah

00:57:05.672 --> 00:57:09.509 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
has guided his people in modern times.

00:57:09.509 --> 00:57:11.544 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Before we conclude,

00:57:11.544 --> 00:57:13.880 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we’ll visit the remote translation office

00:57:13.880 --> 00:57:17.484 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in Chinle, Arizona, in the United States.

00:57:17.484 --> 00:57:21.221 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Located
in the southwestern part of the country,

00:57:21.221 --> 00:57:23.223 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the region is home

00:57:23.223 --> 00:57:26.426 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to many native peoples and tribes.

00:57:26.426 --> 00:57:30.797 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
European settlers arrived in the 1500’s.

00:57:30.797 --> 00:57:33.266 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Throughout the many years since then,

00:57:33.266 --> 00:57:35.268 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
many of the tribes were able

00:57:35.268 --> 00:57:38.471 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to retain their culture and language.

00:57:39.606 --> 00:57:42.308 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Currently,
the United States branch translates

00:57:42.308 --> 00:57:46.279 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
into several indigenous languages, including

00:57:46.279 --> 00:57:50.850 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Cherokee, Hopi, Lakota, and Navajo.

00:57:50.850 --> 00:57:52.986 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
To help with that work,

00:57:52.986 --> 00:57:57.857 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in 2015, a remote translation office, or RTO,

00:57:57.857 --> 00:57:59.893 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
was built in Chinle,

00:57:59.893 --> 00:58:02.896 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
which is in the heart of the Navajo nation.

00:58:02.896 --> 00:58:05.899 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Over 100 volunteers,

00:58:05.899 --> 00:58:08.902 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of which 13 are full-time servants,

00:58:08.902 --> 00:58:10.904 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
work at the RTO.

00:58:11.905 --> 00:58:16.910 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Navajo field has over 430 publishers,

00:58:16.910 --> 00:58:20.346 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
including approximately 130 regular pioneers

00:58:20.346 --> 00:58:23.449 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and some 20 special pioneers.

00:58:23.449 --> 00:58:25.818 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The literature, videos,

00:58:25.818 --> 00:58:28.288 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and audio publications translated

00:58:28.288 --> 00:58:30.290 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
at the RTO

00:58:30.290 --> 00:58:33.259 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
are distributed to 8 Navajo congregations,

00:58:33.259 --> 00:58:38.164 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
11 groups, and 5 pregroups.

00:58:38.164 --> 00:58:41.634 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
For the past five years,
three-day regional conventions

00:58:41.634 --> 00:58:43.836 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
have been held in the Navajo language.

00:58:45.038 --> 00:58:49.042 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In 2018, they had a peak attendance of 471,

00:58:49.042 --> 00:58:52.045 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with one baptized.

00:58:52.045 --> 00:58:54.581 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The volunteers at the RTO in Chinle

00:58:54.581 --> 00:58:59.118 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
send their warm Christian love
to all of us around the world.

00:58:59.118 --> 00:59:02.288 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And we love them dearly.

